    "title": "Frequently Asked Questions",
    "questions": [
      {
        "question": "Is the application really free?",
        "answer": "Yes, the Image Collage Maker is 100% free. There are no hidden costs or premium features."
      },
      {
        "question": "Are my images uploaded to a server?",
        "answer": "No, all images are processed exclusively in your browser. Nothing is uploaded to a server. Your data remains completely private and local on your device."
      },
      {
        "question": "Which image formats are supported?",
        "answer": "The application supports PNG, JPG, and WebP formats. The maximum file size per image is 50MB."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I save my collage and continue editing it later?",
        "answer": "Yes! Use the template library to save your current collage as a template. It will be stored locally in your browser and can be loaded at any time."
      },
      {
        "question": "In which formats can I export my collage?",
        "answer": "You can download your finished collage as PNG, JPEG, or WebP. For JPEG and WebP, you can also adjust the quality."
      },
      {
        "question": "Does the application work offline?",
        "answer": "After the initial page load, the application works offline since all processing happens in the browser. You only need an internet connection for the initial page visit."
      }
    ]
